<sect1 id="gui_menu_Edit" xreflabel="menu item Edit">
	<title>Edit</title>
	<para>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata fileref="gui/menuAndToolbarsFun/images/menu_edit.png" format="PNG"/>
				</imageobject>
				<textobject>
					<phrase>Default menu item - Edit</phrase>
				</textobject>
				<caption><para>Default menu item <emphasis>Edit</emphasis></para></caption>
			</mediaobject>
	</para>

	<variablelist>
		<title>Edit - description of items </title>

		<varlistentry>
			<term id="gui_menu_selectAll" xreflabel="select all objects">Select all objects</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						See <xref linkend="gui_onclickFunctions_selectAll"/>.
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>onSelectMode_AllObjects()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

		<varlistentry>
			<term id="gui_menu_selectGraphical" xreflabel="select graphical operators">Select graphical operators</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						See <xref linkend="gui_onclickFunctions_selectGraphicalOp"/>.
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>onSelectMode_GraphicalOperators()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

		<varlistentry>
			<term id="gui_menu_selectText" xreflabel="select text">Select text</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						See <xref linkend="gui_onclickFunctions_selectText"/>.
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>onSelectMode_Text()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

		<varlistentry>
			<term id="gui_menu_selectAnnot" xreflabel="select annotations">Select annotations</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						See <xref linkend="gui_onclickFunctions_selectAnnotations"/>.
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>onSelectMode_Annot()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

		<varlistentry>
			<term id="gui_menu_setColor" xreflabel="set color">Set color</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						This function set actual <xref linkend="gui_toolbars_foregroundColor"/>
						and <xref linkend="gui_toolbars_backgroundColor"/> to all selected
						operators in actual tab of object tree.
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>setOpColor()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

		<varlistentry>
			<term id="gui_menu_setFont" xreflabel="set font">Set font</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						This function set actual <xref linkend="gui_toolbars_font"/>
						and <xref linkend="gui_toolbars_fontSize"/> to all selected
						text operators in actual tab of object tree.
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>editFontProps()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

		<varlistentry>
			<term>Set relative position of operator</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						Execute dialog to set delta move position, if
						some operators are selected.
						Usefull is moving selected operators direct on
						the page (see <xref linkend="gui_onclickFunctions_selectionModes"/>).
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>moveOperPos()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

		<varlistentry>
			<term>Change relative position</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						Execute dialog to set delta move position, if
						some text operators are selected.
						Usefull is moving selected operators direct on
						the page (see <xref linkend="gui_onclickFunctions_selectionModes"/>).
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>moveTextPos()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

		<varlistentry>
			<term id="gui_menu_dashStyle" xreflabel="dash style">Set line dash style</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						If is selected graphical operators, execute dialog for change
						dash pattern.
						<mediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="gui/menuAndToolbarsFun/images/dialog_dashpattern.png" format="PNG"/>
							</imageobject>
							<textobject>
								<phrase>Dash pattern dialog</phrase>
							</textobject>
							<caption><para>Dash pattern dialog</para></caption>
						</mediaobject>
						After choose dash pattern and confirming its, this dash pattern
						will be set to all selected graphical opeartors.
				</para>
				<para>
						Note: Change dash pattern may result in change dash pattenr some other
						graphical operators (see PdfReference).
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>setDashPattern()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

		<varlistentry>
			<term id="gui_menu_setLineWidth" xreflabel="set line width">Set line width</term>
			<listitem>
				<para>
						Set <xref linkend="gui_toolbars_lineWidth"/> all selected graphical
						operators.
				</para>
				<para>
						Note: Change dash pattern may result in change dash pattenr some other
						graphical operators (see PdfReference).
				</para>
				<para>
						Scripts equivalent: <emphasis>setLineWidth()</emphasis>
				</para>
			</listitem>
		</varlistentry>

	</variablelist>
</sect1>
